Here’s a clean AWS-style architecture diagram (no confusion, no extra components) for your setup:

⸻

🏗️ 🎯 Final Architecture Diagram (Clean)

                   ┌──────────────────────────────┐
                   │   On-Prem Spring Boot API    │
                   │   (Kubernetes Service)       │
                   │                              │
                   │ 1. Call API (JWT)            │
                   │ 2. Receive response          │
                   │ 3. Async download (HTTPS)    │
                   └──────────────┬───────────────┘
                                  │
                                  ▼
        ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
        │ Amazon API Gateway                          │
        │ - JWT / OIDC Authentication                 │
        │ - Secure entry point                        │
        └──────────────┬─────────────────────────────┘
                       │
                       ▼
        ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
        │ AWS Lambda (Reusable Query Executor)        │
        │                                             │
        │ - Load queries config                       │
        │ - Validate params (IDs, limits)             │
        │ - Authorize request                         │
        │ - Execute query                             │
        │                                             │
        │ Decision:                                   │
        │  • No data → return NO_DATA                 │
        │  • Data → store in S3 + presigned URL       │
        └──────────────┬───────────────┬────────────┘
                       │               │
                       │               ▼
                       │     ┌──────────────────────┐
                       │     │ Snowflake Database   │
                       │     │ (Data Source)        │
                       │     └──────────────────────┘
                       │
                       ▼
        ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
        │ Amazon S3 (Private Bucket)                  │
        │ - Stores query results                      │
        │ - Pre-signed URL generated by Lambda        │
        └──────────────┬─────────────────────────────┘
                       │
                       ▼
        ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
        │ Pre-Signed URL (Temporary HTTPS Access)     │
        │ - Valid for limited time (e.g., 5 mins)     │
        │ - No AWS credentials required               │
        └──────────────┬─────────────────────────────┘
                       │
                       ▼
        ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
        │ Spring Boot Async Downloader                │
        │ - HTTP GET download                        │
        │ - Handles large files                      │
        │ - Retry logic                              │
        └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘

⸻

🔄 Simple Flow Summary

1. Spring Boot → calls API Gateway (with JWT auth)
2. API Gateway → invokes Lambda
3. Lambda → runs query on Snowflake
4. If data:
    * store in S3
    * return pre-signed URL
5. Spring Boot → downloads file via HTTPS

⸻

🟢 Final One-Line Architecture

👉 API Gateway → Lambda → Snowflake → S3 → Pre-signed URL → Spring Boot download

⸻

